<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11437472-shivaprakash"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1357452168i/11437472._UY100_CR11,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11437472-shivaprakash">Shivaprakash</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">As Owen mentioned, yes, partially. It draws on a variety of &apos;lessons&apos; he learnt primarily during his test pilot and astronaut days. A very interesting<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">As Owen mentioned, yes, partially. It draws on a variety of 'lessons' he learnt primarily during his test pilot and astronaut days. A very interesting (and exciting!) read, at least for me. Definitely a must read if you are a space enthusiast; this one goes right up there with Carl Sagan's Cosmos in my library. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
