<div id="review_2392422965" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2392422965" />
    <a title="Sad Sunday (Books? Me?!? NEVER!!!) " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22985424-sad-sunday-books-me-never"><img alt="Sad Sunday (Books? Me?!? NEVER!!!) " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544800600p2/22985424.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2392422965?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sad Sunday (Books? Me?!? NEVER!!!) " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sad Sunday (Books? Me?!? NEVER!!!) " href="/user/show/22985424-sad-sunday-books-me-never">Sad Sunday (Books? Me?!? NEVER!!!) </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Sad by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/13716524-evelina-avalinahsbooks">Evelina | AvalinahsBooks</a>
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2392422965" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10825902443230934873">Chris Hadfield might not be the best writer but he is an interesting person and a great storyteller. I consider him to be a very well-round person - his fields of expertise reach far beyond being an astronaut. The book had it&apos;s flaws - it feels like it&apos;s been written in one sitting, there were moments I wanted to know more and moments when less information would have sufficed, some ideas repeat themselves (be prepared, always learn) over and over, but it&apos;s an amazing glimpse into the life and ac</span>
  <span id="freeText10825902443230934873" style="display:none">Chris Hadfield might not be the best writer but he is an interesting person and a great storyteller. I consider him to be a very well-round person - his fields of expertise reach far beyond being an astronaut. The book had it's flaws - it feels like it's been written in one sitting, there were moments I wanted to know more and moments when less information would have sufficed, some ideas repeat themselves (be prepared, always learn) over and over, but it's an amazing glimpse into the life and achievements of one astronaut. So many cool facts about the space life that will make you inner geek happy. But well, it might diminish you dream of becoming an astronaut (don't worry, commercial flights are almost now). One of his goals was to bring space exploration "closer" to people and I think he achieved that 100%. <br><br>This is Chris performing David Bowie's "Space Oddity" in space (ISS).<br><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KaOC9danxNo">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KaOC9...</a><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1548407733ra/26967978.gif" width="300" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="10825902443230934873" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
